Fix richdem's Array2D.hpp to compile against a current GDAL, whose
GDALDataset::GetMetadata returns CSLConstList (const char* const*)
rather than char**. Verified against GDAL 3.13.0 on the dev machine
(gdal_majorobject.h:79). The exact GDAL minor version where the return
type narrowed is not pinned; the justification rests on the GDAL
actually in use. See the repository root README.md, section
"C++ patches", for the full rationale.

**Status:** REQUIRED before building the helper tools (or upstream's
own fsm.exe) against a modern GDAL. There is no bundled/patched copy of
the C++ in this repo; you apply this to your own upstream clone. The
Julia test suite itself (`Pkg.test()`, "Option A") does NOT need this
— it only matters when regenerating oracle data ("Option B"). Do NOT
push upstream.

Apply against the richdem submodule of an upstream clone checked out at
the pinned commit (parent Barnes2020-FillSpillMerge
`1c499ea475c09b9f4c5da74ee5cc995de169db63`, which pins richdem to
`415032db2f30372111e4cfd37f046e7542ed66f3`):

  cd <upstream-clone>/submodules/dephier/submodules/richdem
  git apply <FSM_Julia>/tools/patches/richdem-gdal-cslconstlist.patch

